The  '''Banda Sea monarch''' ('''''Symposiachrus mundus'''''), formerly known as the '''black-bibbed monarch''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Monarchidae]] that is [[Endemism|endemic]] to Indonesia. It is found in the [[Tanimbar Islands]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical mangrove forests.<ref name=iucn/>

==Taxonomy and systematics==
This species was formerly placed in the genus ''[[Monarcha]]'' until moved to ''Symposiachrus'' in 2009.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldbirdnames.org/Archives/Master_IOC_list_v2.0.xls|title=IOC Bird List v2.0|date=2009|access-date=28 October 2016}}</ref> 

